                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.0012Anti-War/336: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Herrick</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="24" xml:id="d135fn24">Repeated by the Department to the missions
                        concerned, Aug. 27, 1 p.m.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-08-27T15:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 27, 1928—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 27—12:12 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>265. The Secretary asks that the following message from him be sent at once to
                    all missions to which the circular telegram of August 16, 11 p.m., was sent
                    direct by the Department. Missions reached via Paris are being instructed from
                    here: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Anti-war treaty signed this afternoon. Please deliver as soon as
                            possible the note transmitted in the Department’s circular telegram of
                            August 16, 11 p.m., dating the note today August 27, 1928. Do not fail
                            to transmit French text of the treaty at the same time. Frank B.
                            Kellogg, Secretary of State.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Herrick</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
